<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="44" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
Pfeiffer did not state on how many specimens his description was based, but from his dimensions it is clear that he had more than one specimen at hand. From 
<bibRefCitation author="Pfeiffer, L" journalOrPublisher="Monographia heliceorum viventium: sistens descriptiones systematicas et criticas omnium huius familiae generum et specierum hodie cognitarum" pageId="50" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 920" refId="B89" refString="Pfeiffer, L, 1859. . Monographia heliceorum viventium: sistens descriptiones systematicas et criticas omnium huius familiae generum et specierum hodie cognitarum 4: 1 - 920" volume="4" year="1859">Pfeiffer (1859)</bibRefCitation>
it becomes clear that this was one of the taxa described from &quot;Mus. Cuming&quot;. 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 255" refId="B9" refString="Breure, ASH, 1978. Notes on and descriptions of Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 164: 1 - 255" title="Notes on and descriptions of Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda)." volume="164" year="1978">Breure (1978)</bibRefCitation>
re-described the species on the basis of additional material and established the first exact locality in state 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo. The current systematic position follows 
<bibRefCitation author="Simone, LRL" journalOrPublisher="EGB / Fapesp, Sao Paulo" pageId="52" pageNumber="69" refId="B121" refString="Simone, LRL, 2006. Land and freshwater molluscs of Brazil. EGB/Fapesp, Sao Paulo" title="Land and freshwater molluscs of Brazil." year="2006">Simone (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, whose reference to the figured type as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“syntype”">&quot;syntype&quot;</normalizedToken>
is erroneous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
